Now I really enjoy the sound. So yes, you can EQ the sound to your liking. The sound may not be as clean as high fidelity IEM, but very good and sufficient for daily listening in office and during commuting. ANC is very effective. I have Jabra Elite 7 Pro and Liberty 5 ANC is superior. Call quality is good. The only gripe is the pinch control. Need to get used to it and know where to pinch. Connection not much diff w BT 5.x.in terms of range. App is feature rich. But coming from Jabra, I just hope the side tone level can be adjusted. For Liberty, if you turn on the call awareness, it means it turn on aware mode at full blast. So a bit distracting for call. I end up turned it off. Overall I am very satisfied with Liberty 5 and recommend it for the price. Oh.. battery life is superb!

Really worth your money. I purchased this for the sake of having a clear mic and crisp sound for online class. But it's so much better than that. The dolby atmos setting helps you achieve a better sound quality when listening or watching, or even gaming. 

The charging time is short, and the listening hours last long. The best part also is the Noise Cancelling and transparency option. In a busy cafe, I can just set my noise cancelling mode to a 5, and at work, I shift to transparency mode where I can listen to everyone while also having music being played. 

When I remove even one earbud from my ear, the device automatically detects it and pauses the song. 

It has a lot of really great features that only a buyer could experience. Very worth the money.

Considering the skirt material is linen, it is best to avoid spraying oil/alcohol perfume because it can leave stains on the fabric.

Overall, for the quality at this price, it's really fitting. But if you are looking for a tighter and straighter material, usually the price is definitely more expensive too.
